York takes over with 58 seconds left. They will kneel and improve to 7-1. FINAL: 45-17 York takes down Westwood.
York adds on with a 43-yard TD run from JT Sander. 45-17 with 3:20 left.
York adds to the lead with that 32-yard FG from Ruiz. Cougars lead 38-17. 4Q
Westwood was driving and had the ball at the 21, but Heatley throws an errant pass that's picked off by Max Necklen. York ball at their 24.
York strikes again. Stephen Oglesby with the 1-yard run. York leads 35-17 with 2:59 left in 3Q.
The second half is underway, and York forces a fumble that leads to a 22-yard pass from McKinney to JT Sander. 28-17 York lead.

I was out in Chester to see @CHSCyclonesFB beat Columbia, 48-28, for a big homecoming victory. Game story here... https:// twitter.com/RHHerald_Preps /status/916496796632969216 …
Columbia scored on Goodwin's 3-yard TD to make the score 48-28. And that will be the final score. Chester picks up the lopsided win.
Clock is now running here in the second half.
Erby with his 6th TD (4 rush, 2 pass) on the night. Took it to the house on that 5-yard TD run to the right. PAT is blocked. 48-21 Chester
The second half is underway, and Columbia will start the ball.
Erby is 12-for-21 with 206 yds and has 97 rushing yards on 13 attempts. He has 5 total TD (3 rush, 2 pass) with 1 INT.
We finally reach the half and Chester leads 42-21.
And TJ Hollis picks it off for the Cyclones. Chester ball with 15 seconds left in the half.
Well, if I could count properly, it's actually 22 unanswered points for Chester.
Chester now has 23 unanswered points after that Erby to Hardin 40-yard connection. Cyclones lead Columbia 42-21, :52 left in 2Q
And Erby capitalizes on Jackson's fumble recovery with a 1-yard TD run. He passes it to Hardin for the 2-pt. 34-21 Chester. 2:40 in 2Q
Jackson goes down with an injury on the play and is being assisted off the field. No weight on his left leg. Chester ball at the 1.
Chester back with the ball. Javonti Jackson scoops up a fumble on the first play and goes 19 yards before diving and missing the endzone.
What a game. Chester answers right back. 21-yard pass from Erby to T. Mills gives S. Mills the opp. to punch it in from the 4. 26-21 Chester
He does have a leg. Just kicked it out of the end zone on the kickoff. https:// twitter.com/RHHerald_Preps /status/916458371414417410 …
Rico Dorsey's 1st carry of the game goes for 74 yards up the sideline and a score. Kick is good. Columbia takes the lead, 21-20. 4:42 2Q

John Erby with the nice read and cut upfield for the 17-yard TD run. The kick is no good. 20-14 Chester. 6:19 2Q
A promising Chester drive is ended by a pick by Columbia's Alex Martin. However, on the first play, Puch fumbles the handoff. Chester ball.
Quay Hardin with the gutsy return. Kick is deep, which threw off Chester and stopped at the 1. Hardin picked it up & got to the 19.
Thomas Green caps an 80-yard drive for Columbia with a 1-yard TD. Kick is good. 14-14. :04 left in 1Q
Erby then punches it in from the 10-yard line, and Chester converts the 2-pt conversion. 14-7 Chester. 5:14 left 1Q.
Erby busts out a 19-yard run and is helped by 15-yard late hit followed by a 5-yard offsides penalty to put the ball on 10.
Columbia strikes back. They open up with a 60-run on 1st play, then score on a Thomas Green 5-yard run. 7-6, Columbia leads. 6:29 left 1Q.
Chester strikes 1st with a 41-yard pass from Erby to Zion Mills. Mills burnt the defense for the easy score. Kick was blocked. 6-0, Chester
Stan Mills to start at RB in place of Brown.

Right you are. Meant to say to Scott. Washington PAT is no good." Good looking out."
Chester escapes 40-39. They scored 34 points in the second half to beat Lower Richland.
Lower Richland got a nice bounce, but Chester snags it and they will most likely take the W.
Off-setting penalties. Chester will receive the kick. On-side coming.
Chester stops the 2-point conversion and keeps the lead 40-39. BUT, the entire Chester team rushed the field and a flag is thrown. :23 left.
Higgins connects with Jacobs on a 50-yard pass and then a 10-yard TD connection on 4th down with 31 seconds left. 40-39 Chester. PAT coming.
Big defensive stop for the Cyclones. They take over on down with 3:15 left in the game. They lead 40-33.
Chester answers with a 61-yard TD pass from Erby to TJ Hollis. Hollis was wide open for the score. 40-33 Chester lead.
LR kills 5 minutes on that TD drive that finished with a 10-yard run from Tyler Singleton. 2-pt pass failed. 34-33 Chester. 7:07 4Q
Pha'Leak Brown is having himself a night with 196 total yards (158 rush, 38 rec.) and 2 TD.
Erby to Pha'Leak Brown for another 30-yard TD pass. Two-point conversion fails. Chester leads 34-27 with 11:24 left in the game.
We're headed into the 4th. Chester 28-27.
Lower Richland has an answer. Keyshawn Capers caps the drive with a 3-yard TD run. LR converts the 2-point conversion. Chester 28-27.
The crew in the box agree with that assessment. https:// twitter.com/RHHerald_Preps /status/908865746490585088 …
Cyclones score for the 3rd time here in the 3rd Q. Erby caps the drive with a 23-yard pass to TJ Hollis. Chester leads 28-19.
Pha'Leak Brown just continues to plow through Lower Richland defenders. He has 11 for 150 and 1 TD.
Chester definitely has woken up in the second half.
Quay Hardin with the 20-yard TD from Erby and a little extra effort to shake the defender. Chester leads for the first time tonight, 21-19.
The Cyclones started that drive on the 35-yard line after pinning LR on the 4-yard line to start the half.
Chester takes advantage of great field position and uses an 18-yard TD run from Erby to start the scoring in 3Q. 2pt pass makes it 19-14 LR.

Chester Leaders: Passing-J. Erby (5-8, 45 yd) Rush-Erby (9 rush, 19 yds) P. Brown (4 rush, 88 yds) Rec.- Five players with 1 Rec.
Chester unable to pick up any points on the final drive of the half with the 28-yd FG wide right. LR leads 19-6 heading into halftime.
LR recovers the fumble on Chester's punt and converts it into a 30-yard TD pass from Higgins to Goodwin on 4th Down. 19-6 with :41 left, 2Q.
On 1st play of 2Q, Pha'Leak Brown takes it 74 yards and 2 plays later punches it in with a 12-yard run. PAT no good. LR leads Chester 13-6.
With more than 4 minutes left in the 1Q, Lower Richland's Higgins already has 133 rushing yards.
Lower Richland QB Tevaughn Higgins busts out an 83-yard scramble up the middle to give LR the 13-0 lead in the 1Q vs. Chester.
Lower Richland strikes first with a 12-yard TD pass from Higgins to Washington. PAT is no good. LR leads Chester, 6-0.
A 46-yard TD rush by Pha'Leak Brown is called back for a penalty that stalls Chester's opening drive.
Lower Richland deferred the kick and Chester will receive to begin the game.

Wild game tonight freelancing for @RHHerald . Clover (3-0) beat Hunter-Huss, 42-41, in OT… https://www. instagram.com/p/BYkM5ZYn-rT/
And Clover stuffs Danner at the goalline. Clover beats Hunter Huss, 42-41 in OT.
Zo Wallace with a 1-yard QB sneak and Hunter Huss will try for the win as they look to go for two points. 42-41 Clover.
Clover strikes first in OT with a 10-yard rush from QB Garrett Miller. 42-35 Clover.
We are heading to overtime here in Clover. Teams are knotted up 35-35. Each team will get 4 downs from the 10-yard line.
Wow. Tony Davis runs back a kick 100 yards for a touchdown, but it is called back. Would've given Huss the lead.
Clover ties it back up with a powerful 23-yard run from Soph. RB David Hall. 35-35; 4:14 4Q
Clover does not have an answer for Chandler, who has 5 carries for 165 and 3 catches for 70 yards. 5 total TDs on the night (2 rec./3 rush)
Chandler continues his dominance with a 40-yard scramble up the middle to give Huss the 35-28 lead. 7:06 left in 4Q.
Hunter Huss opts for an onside/squib kick and recovers it. Will start the drive on Clover's 41-yard line. All momentum on Huss' side.
Huss ties the game up with a big 28-yard scramble from Chandler. Now has 125 yards rushing to go along with 70 rec. yds. 28-28; 7:24 left
The gloves are off here as we head into the 4Q. Both teams are with a few big plays to ignite the crowd.
Clover still leads 28-21 with less than a minute left in the 3Q.
But Huss answers right back. Chandler entered at QB and went with the QB draw for an 80-yard TD run right up the middle on the first play.
Another Miller to Lane TD connection. This time a 24-yard pass and catch to give Clover the 28-14 lead. 1:14 3Q
Big momentum shift for Clover with a deflected pass that lands in the hands of Jay Falls. He runs it back for 39 yds to Huss' 24-yard line.
Hunter Huss' Zo Wallace connects with Crawford Chandler for the 2nd time tonight on that 15-yard TD pass. 21-14 Clover. 6:57 left in 3Q
Second half is underway with a nice 40-yard return from Huss' Davis.
Clover's Jaylin Lane leading the way with 3 catches for 53 yards and 1 TD. While Huss' Crawford leads all WR with 55 yds on 2 catches.
@CHS_BlueEagles head into half leading Huss, 21-7. Miller leading with 7-for-16, 93 yds passing, 35 rushing yards and 3 TD (2 rush, 1 pass).
On the 2nd play of the drive, Miller connects with Jaylin Lane for a 43-yd TD. Clover goes up 21-7 with 1:28 left in the half.
Both of Clover's TDs have come via runs from QB Garrett Miller.
Garrett Miller with a powerful 24-yard TD scramble with a couple nice cuts and some help from his O-Line near the end. 14-7 Clover. 2:47 2Q
Huss' Wallace tries to pitch the ball on the 1st play of the 2Q, but a fumble is picked up by Clover. Two plays later, Clover coughs it back
As time expires in the 1Q, Clover's Miller ran the QB sneak to tie the game at 7-7.
Clover went from their 41 to Hunter Huss' 26 on that punt fumble, and is looking to tie the game.
Wild play. Clover goes 3-and-out. Gets the punt off, a roughing the kicker. Penalty was declined after Hunter Huss fumbled and lost the punt
Zo Wallace hits Crawford Chandler for a 30-yd TD. Chandler has 55 yards on the day. 2:59 left in the first.
Solid drive is stalled for Clover after Jaylin Lane makes the catch but fumbles around the 50. Hunter Huss converts the TO into a TD. 7-0 HH
Senior Devon Chisholm is hurt on the 3rd down play and is being helped off the field.
Clover fails to score on the opening drive for the first time all year.
Senior Semaj Lakin took the kickoff for a 29-yard return and the Blue Eagle will start at the 40.
Looks like @CHS_BlueEagles won the toss and elected to receive.
The @CHS_BlueEagles just ran out of the Blue Eagle tunnel, and we're just minutes away. Clover is riding a 6 quarter shutout streak.
Here at Memorial Stadium for Clover-Hunter Huss. Last night was postponed, but kick will be at 7:00 tonight. Both teams are 2-0. pic.twitter.com/w6EuKsLLI6
